# SCSS Ownership Contract (Mandatory)

Every SCSS file owns exactly one component. Styling responsibilities are non-overlapping.

## Geometry ownership

- Layout containers own columns, gaps, breakpoints only.
- State-frame components own loading/error/empty/selection visuals only.
- Domain items own domain-specific visuals (typography, icons, media details) only.
- Any CSS property defined in exactly one component layer. Duplicate ownership = blocker.

## Typography ownership

`h1`–`h6` get `font-size`, `font-weight`, `line-height` **only** from `apps/web/src/styles.scss`. Component SCSS must never redeclare these on heading selectors. Variant scales: add modifier class to `styles.scss`.

## Intermediate wrapper rule

Wrappers (JS hooks, directives, state layers, ng-content) carry **zero styling**. Exception: one property with a comment explaining why it can't live on layout owner or content element.

## Two-element rule

Only two elements carry geometry: (1) outermost layout owner, (2) innermost content element. Everything between: zero styling.

## CSS Layer Architecture

- `@layer components` — geometry, layout, default visuals
- `@layer states` — state-driven visuals only
- State selectors must not change geometry. Geometry stays stable in components layer.

## Comment contract

Every CSS class, custom property, and keyframe: two comment lines above (what it does + spec reference).

```scss
// Defines column layout for grid-md mode, 3 columns with token-based gap
// @see item-grid.md#layout-modes
.item-grid--grid-md { ... }
```
